  "title": "DTQEM v16.0 - Synchronized Two-Times Model (Effective Lindblad Framework for Measurement-Controlled Tunneling)",
  "description": "This release presents a clean, efficient 2x2 Lindblad model for quantum tunneling under continuous measurement. The observer strength E_ext (0 to 1) controls two effects simultaneously: Effective Hamiltonian H_eff = (Delta/2)(1-E_ext)sigma_x (reduces tunneling rate) and Lindblad operator L = sqrt(gamma0 E_ext) sigma_z (increases pure dephasing, true Zeno mechanism). Key numerical results (Delta=3.5 meV, gamma0=5e10 per second, t=20 ps): E_ext=0.0 -> P=0.0532 (free Rabi, destructive phase); E_ext=0.3 -> 0.2872 (partial decoherence); E_ext=0.5 -> 0.7943 (synchronisation peak, times balanced); E_ext=0.7 -> 0.2774 (near-Zeno); E_ext=1.0 -> 0.0000 (complete Zeno freeze). The model unifies the quantum Zeno effect, quantum eraser, and wave-particle duality under the concept of temporal balance: observer time V = E_ext, particle time D = 1-E_ext, with V + D = 1. All code is open source, numerically verified (error ~2e-14 versus analytical Rabi oscillation), and ready for experimental validation.",
